$ /usr/share

`/usr/share` contains subdirectories with specific application data that can be shared among different architectures of the same OS.

sa:

  Subdirectories of `/usr/share` include
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/applications[`applications`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/ca-certificates[`ca-certificates`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/cups[`cups`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/distro-info[`info`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/dict[`dict`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/doc[`doc`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/fonts[`fonts`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/hwdata[`hwdata`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/keyrings[`keyrings`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/icons[`icons`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/mime[`mime`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/man[`man`]: the directory for → Linux/man-page[man pages].
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/misc[`misc`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/pixmaps[`pixmaps`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/pkgconfig[`pkgconfig`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/ppd[`ppd`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/terminfo[`terminfo`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/xml[`xml`]
    • → Linux/fhs/usr/share/xsessions[`xsessions`]

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/`, → Linux/fhs
